fields.title: All families are unique and so are their paths to creating a family. Was {{hidden:child}} conceived with the help of egg, sperm or embryo donation?

Congratulations. While all children are miracles, we think donor-conceived children are even more miraculous

It's important to tell your child about their conception via egg, sperm or embryo donation early in their lives (ideally before the age of 5), so that when they find out about their genetic origin, it isn't a shock to them, or perceived as duplicity by their parents, which risks harming their relationship with you. Many also argue that it's the child's right to know.

While it's not always easy to talk to your child about something this personal, as well as abstract, this book will tell your child's unique story in a way that'll make {{hidden:child}} feel good about it and build trust. The book will show {{hidden:child}} at the very centre of your family, strengthening their identity and sense of belonging.
_*More information about telling can be found on the Donor Conception Network's website at  www.dcnetwork.org*_
